# Pre-Deploy Checklist

Before every deploy (`./scripts/deploy.sh`), ensure these stay in sync:

## Version Bump
1. `deploy/js/utils/brand.js` → `VERSION` constant
2. `MANIFEST.md` → Version field in Identity table

Both must show the same version string.

## Changelog
- `deploy/changelog.html` — Add a new card **above** previous entries
- Version tag and date must match the `VERSION` in `brand.js`
- Each line item must correspond to an actual committed change
- Use `plus` icon (emerald) for new features, `refresh-cw` icon (blue) for changes/refactors

## Features Page
- `deploy/features.html` — Update if the change adds, removes, or modifies user-facing capabilities
- Skip if the change is purely internal (refactor, bug fix, data update)

## Git Alignment
- The version in code must match the git tag / commit message
- Commit message format: `v0.x.x — Short description of what changed`
- Do NOT deploy uncommitted changes — commit first, then deploy

## Deploy Command
After committing, provide the user with a ready-to-copy deploy command:
```
cd /Users/rickwichgers/Documents/AI-tools/advanced-plus && quick deploy dist/ advanced-vs-plus
```
The deploy script (`./scripts/deploy.sh`) requires interactive confirmation, so always give the user a direct command to run in their terminal. Run the build step first (`rsync -a --exclude='client/' deploy/ dist/`) if dist/ is stale.
